<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-0601 </DOCNO><TEXT>On the night of 23/24 February 1987 a new supernova called SN 1987A, wasdiscovered. Within a few hours of the announcement of the discovery,the South African Astronomical Observatory (SAAO) began a series of observations.In this article, the importance of supernovae-exploding stars, and whatthe SAAO has discovered so far from SN 1987A are discussed.</TEXT></DOC>